FBIS4-61131 "drsov086_t_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia 28 Reported HIV-Positive; 1 AIDS Carrier 28 Reported HIV-Positive; 1 AIDS Carrier WS0405074894 Tallinn ETA in English 1849 GMT 3 May 94 WS0405074894 Tallinn ETA English BFN ["News Release"] [Text] In Estonia there are, at present, 28 HIV-infected people and one person who has developed AIDS, Jaan Martin from the State AIDS Centre told ETA, on Tuesday [3 May]. Martin said that a total of 34 virus-infected people have been registered in Estonia, the first already in 1988. Three of the infected have left Estonia and two have died, which leaves us with 28 infected and one who has developed AIDS. All infected have got their infection through sexual relations. According to different estimates about 2.5 million people in the whole world have developed AIDS, of which 850,000 have been registered officially. HIV infected amount to about 14 million.
